cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper proposes a new method for optimizing constellation design using unsupervised machine learning to mitigate nonlinear effects in fiber channels. This involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT, followed by cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.SI, and cs.DS.
